# Kairos Ontology Toolkit — AI Provider Configuration
# Copy this file as .env and fill in the values for your environment.
# Do NOT commit .env to source control.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AI Provider Selection
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supported values: github, azure, foundry
# Default: github (if GITHUB_TOKEN is set)
# KAIROS_AI_PROVIDER=github

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GitHub Models (default)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Uses GitHub's inference API at https://models.inference.ai.azure.com
# Requires a GitHub PAT with Models API access.
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Azure AI Foundry (legacy OpenAI-compatible endpoint)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Uses your Azure AI Foundry deployment endpoint with the OpenAI SDK directly.
# Set both AZURE_AI_ENDPOINT and AZURE_AI_KEY, or configure managed identity.
# AZURE_AI_ENDPOINT=https://your-project.services.ai.azure.com/models
# AZURE_AI_KEY=your-api-key-here

# For managed identity (no key needed):
# Install: pip install kairos-ontology-toolkit[azure]
# Then just set AZURE_AI_ENDPOINT — DefaultAzureCredential handles auth.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Microsoft Foundry (recommended for enterprise)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Uses the azure-ai-projects SDK with the Foundry project endpoint.
# Install: pip install kairos-ontology-toolkit[foundry]
#
# Format: https://<resource>.services.ai.azure.com/api/projects/<project>
#
# KAIROS_AI_PROVIDER=foundry
# AZURE_FOUNDRY_ENDPOINT=https://your-resource.services.ai.azure.com/api/projects/your-project
#
# Entra ID auth (recommended — and required by the Foundry SDK):
# The azure-ai-projects SDK authenticates with an AAD token (DefaultAzureCredential),
# so just set AZURE_FOUNDRY_ENDPOINT and sign in with `az login` (or use a managed
# identity). Requires the "Foundry User" (or higher) RBAC role on the resource.
#
# AZURE_FOUNDRY_API_KEY is best-effort only: the Foundry SDK's get_openai_client()
# needs a token credential, so a key cannot authenticate on this path — when set it
# is tried and then automatically falls back to DefaultAzureCredential.
# AZURE_FOUNDRY_API_KEY=your-api-key-here

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Model override (optional — default: gpt-5.4-mini)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# KAIROS_AI_MODEL=gpt-5.4-mini

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Per-role endpoints (optional — issue #182)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The two LLM-powered pre-modeling steps have different accuracy/cost profiles
# and can each use their own endpoint + model:
#
#   * affinity  (analyse-sources)   — coarse table → domain classification; the
#     high-volume call. A small model (gpt-5.4-mini) is the right default.
#   * alignment (propose-alignment) — closed-vocabulary matching (pick the right
#     ref_class, map every column). Accuracy-sensitive — prefer a strong
#     *non-reasoning* model (gpt-5.4), optionally on a separate deployment.
#     Reasoning models (gpt-5.5+) add latency/cost without benefit here.
#
# If a role's *_ENDPOINT is set, that OpenAI-compatible endpoint + key is used for
# that step. If only *_MODEL is set, the role keeps the global provider above but
# overrides just the model. Anything unset falls back to the global config.
#
# Affinity step (keep it cheap):
# KAIROS_AI_AFFINITY_MODEL=gpt-5.4-mini
# KAIROS_AI_AFFINITY_ENDPOINT=https://your-mini-deployment.services.ai.azure.com/models
# KAIROS_AI_AFFINITY_KEY=your-affinity-key
#
# Alignment step (upgrade for accuracy):
# KAIROS_AI_ALIGNMENT_MODEL=gpt-5.4
# KAIROS_AI_ALIGNMENT_ENDPOINT=https://your-strong-deployment.services.ai.azure.com/models
# KAIROS_AI_ALIGNMENT_KEY=your-alignment-key
